<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-16-0845 </DOCNO><TEXT>Environmental problems created by energy development are divided intofour key areas - global effects, local effects, atmospheric pollutionand radioactive wastes. Possible solutions to these problems are discussed- production and use limits; energy substitution; reduction of atmosphericemissions; mitigation of environmental effects. Comparative evaluations,with respect to environmental effects, are provided for various energysources. It is recommended that pollution control agencies be establishedto ensure effective adherence to pollution standards and laws.</TEXT></DOC>